# GitHub CLI comment/body safety

## Always use a heredoc for `gh ... --body`
- Do **not** embed `\n` in a quoted string and expect GitHub to render newlines.
- Do **not** inline Markdown backticks (`` `code` ``) inside a double-quoted shell string; bash will treat backticks as command substitution unless protected.

## Safe template (preferred)
Use a single-quoted heredoc delimiter to prevent interpolation:

```bash
gh <cmd> ... --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
First line

- Bullet 1
- Bullet 2 with `inline_code`

Refs #1234
EOF
)"
```

## Notes
- Prefer `Refs #<n>` when you only want a link.
- Prefer `Fixes #<n>` / `Closes #<n>` when you want GitHub to auto-link in the Issue **Development** section and auto-close the issue on merge.
